data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Projzilla uses bugzilla searches to generate the project file. You will need to perform an existing search and save the results to your computer. These saved results are then loaded and parsed by Projzilla.
The results can be saved in XML or CSV format from Bugzilla. When savings as CSV, ensure that all the fields are displayed in your search results.
It is recommended that the search results are saved in XML because it contains more information.

data.name: textBox4.Text
data.value: Create the project file which will receive the bugzilla information. You can choose to either generate to an existing project file or generate to a new file. If you are generating to a new file, the file name must be specified ahead of time.

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value: Everything is now ready for you to generate a project file. Click Generate to create the project file. Please ensure that Microsoft Project is not already running. Generation will: launch project, import the bugzilla data, then quit project.
